<P>To this victory, that supreme vertue is also co~ducent, which di|recteth <NOTE PLACE="marg">Before all thinges we must obey the calling of God.</NOTE> vs to follow in all things, the good pleasure and calling of God: who alwaies calleth vs to mortification of our affections, and to those exercises, by which it is attained: neither accepteth he any externall obedience, vnles first we satisfie his calling. Ther|fore the seruat of the Lord ought alwaies to haue before his eies
