<P>What I say of the Clergy, I s<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> <NOTE PLACE="marg">How farre children ought to o|bey their parents in this matter.</NOTE> also of sonnes and daughters, w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> are also vnder the gouernment<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> parents, if perhaps by them the be hardly delt with, that now <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> then they may giue the~selues v<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> to prayer. For although it be n<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> lawfull for them not to obay, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> to striue against their parents: y<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> it is lawfull sometimes to besto<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> some timevpon this exercise: lea<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> perchance they fal into that da<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> gerous hardnes of heart, of whi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> we haue spoken before. For th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> misery of man is so great, th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> world so peruerse, and dange<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> are so common, that if wee b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> a little estrange our selues fro<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> God, great perill hangeth ou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">
