<P>Furthermore as no end is to b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> preferred before this, so neyth<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> are other businesses and occup<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> tions to be preferred before th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> exercises and meanes, by whi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> this end is obtayned. Whatso<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> uer is in the world, is accident<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> and vnstable: onely the loue God mounteth aboue all thing<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> ruleth &amp; preuaileth in all thin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> and gouerneth all things. Th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> is not any sinne more grieuo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> then to place Dagon by the A<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> of the couenaunt, as the <HI>P<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> stines</HI> did: but the Arke of couenant is to be seated in a m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">
