to be esteemed of her husban<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> which doth that she ought and meete, hauing her husbande a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> waies before her eies, who almo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> euery houre bestoweth gifts an<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> benefits vpon her: or she, that farre off from her husband, wh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> among many letters, scarce rece<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> ueth one from him, and yet ne<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> uerthelesse continueth vnto hi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> firme in her loue, and steedfast i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> her fidelity? Then much mor<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> glorious shal that soule be whic<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> by manye daies being seperate<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> from her bridegroome, yet sti<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> preserueth her innocency, saying with <HI>Iob, Loe, though he slay m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"></HI> <NOTE PLACE="marg">Iob. 13.</NOTE> <HI>yet will I trust in him.</HI></P>
