<P>Ye say that sanctity consistet <NOTE PLACE="marg">Diuine co~|solations for what they are profitable.</NOTE> not in spirituall consolations Surely it is true, that sanctity co<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> sisteth not in them, but yet the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> bring a great helpe vnto sanctity perfection is not placed in the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> but yet they are principall instr<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">|ments for the attaintment of pe<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">|fection.</P>
