<P>Ye say that the perfection of a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">hristian life is not placed in ma|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> consolations, but in bearing <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">tiently, when they are denyed. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">either can I deny this: but to|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">ther with this patience great <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">igence must be ioined: that the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">ace lost may be recouered, that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">al times we may bee ready for <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">e diuine worship and ministery. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">r vnlesse there had beene great <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">ckes and motiues, which stirre a man with great alacritye to
