<P>But I demaund of them, w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> so feare; What doe you feare, a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> why doe you feare&punc; if ye shall s<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> that ye feare those thinges, th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> are of another life: it is certay<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> that nothing can hurt thee, wit<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">|out the consent and license of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> Lord of all thinges. But if he <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> punish ye, hee can doe it eu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> where, &amp; at al times: i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> he wil<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> punish ye, neither the oportun<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> of the place, nor the mallice <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 word"> your aduersaries can hurt you<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> without him none hath powe<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> harme you.</P>
